article.headline: Cleveland St. 79, Norfolk State 47
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- Modibo Niakate scored a career-high 31 points and Cleveland State opened both halves with 11-0 runs to beat Norfolk State 79-47 Saturday. Raheem Moss had 12 points and Omari Westley added 10 points for Cleveland State (2-0). Calvin Brown led Norfolk State (0-2) with nine points. Bass Dieng had eight points and Chakowby Hicks had seven. The Vikings kept Norfolk State scoreless for more than five minutes at the opening of the game. Cleveland State led at halftime 35-26 and extended the lead to 46-26 with 12 minutes left by opening the second half with a 11-0 run. Cleveland State, which had a season-best 11 steals in three games last year, got 14 against Norfolk state.
